{
  "stem": "166.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 16.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I come into town-- to my hometown.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember, I walk on the street and I don't know where to go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't see a single Jew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I thought I am the only Jew that survived.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I go the place where it was the Jewish Community Center, and I look up and, finally, one guy comes by on a bike and he says to me, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I said, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He says, come with me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he took me to the place where-- there was another place-- a small community center where there were maybe 30 or 35 Jews in the whole town.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they gave me 50 zlotys, and they give me some cards to buy food-- stamps to buy food-- because without stamps you couldn't get a ration card, like rations.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Without this you couldn't get-- and he says, you can sleep in this and this place, this [INAUDIBLE] where there were beds like for the army, you know?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like a barracks.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, like a barracks.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this was a high-rise building.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It used to be the City Hall before there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I go to sleep over there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I found-- my friends came in next day, Abe Frosch and his brother and [INAUDIBLE] came in, and we went to school together.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So these were my closest that we found each other.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were there maybe a week in Bedzin, and we had to stay to go to the orphanage house for soup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, from the ration cards, with 50 zlotys what could you buy?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Practically it was not enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So we went back to Germany, maybe to find somebody or to get something or-- so went back to-- we went to Breslau.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
